WEBVTT

00:01.290 --> 00:02.874
- Jeff.
- Jessica, you were right.

00:02.958 --> 00:05.660
We either need to have both,
or it's not going to work.

00:05.744 --> 00:08.830
Effective immediately,
I'm tendering my resignation.

00:08.914 --> 00:10.665
Forstman
doesn't throw money around

00:10.799 --> 00:12.383
without getting something
in return.

00:12.468 --> 00:14.419
He's gonna get money
in return.

00:14.503 --> 00:15.420
Money is third on his list.

00:15.504 --> 00:17.222
The first two are
getting back at people

00:17.306 --> 00:18.806
and getting control of people.

00:18.924 --> 00:19.807
You son of a bitch,
you didn't bring me here

00:19.925 --> 00:20.975
for you to sign on the arrows.

00:21.093 --> 00:22.477
You brought me here
for me to sign on the arrows.

00:22.595 --> 00:24.179
Yep.

00:24.313 --> 00:25.393
After Woodall lost his job,

00:25.431 --> 00:27.265
Forstman got him installed
at the SEC.

00:27.399 --> 00:28.399
Where's the proof?

00:28.484 --> 00:29.767
In Eric Woodall's
bank accounts.

00:29.902 --> 00:30.902
This is ridiculous.

00:30.936 --> 00:33.104
I'm your boss.

00:33.239 --> 00:34.359
Gentlemen, give me a minute.

00:34.490 --> 00:35.740
You're forcing me
to turn you in

00:35.824 --> 00:37.108
for what you did
12 years ago.

00:37.193 --> 00:38.276
You're not gonna do that.

00:38.410 --> 00:40.111
Because you
did it too, pal.

00:40.196 --> 00:44.165
Anyone else
ever loses faith in me,

00:44.283 --> 00:45.950
it doesn't matter.

00:46.035 --> 00:47.585
With you, it's different.

00:47.670 --> 00:49.420
I should go.

00:49.538 --> 00:50.622
Why?

00:50.706 --> 00:53.124
You know
I love you, Donna.

