To Harvey.

01:20.869 --> 01:24.539
To Harvey. Cheers.

01:24.657 --> 01:32.547
♪ ♪

01:46.345 --> 01:47.929
Jay, can I get
a Macallan 18?

01:50.316 --> 01:52.517
You know, usually when someone
wins their first trial,

01:52.651 --> 01:54.519
they at least pretend
to finish the drink

01:54.653 --> 01:56.070
their fellow ADAs bought them.

01:56.188 --> 01:57.188
I'm sorry, do we--

01:57.189 --> 01:58.856
Know each other?
Not yet.

01:59.024 --> 01:59.941
But today's your lucky day.

02:00.025 --> 02:01.242
And why is that?

02:01.360 --> 02:03.328
Because it's the day
you get to meet Donna.

02:03.412 --> 02:05.196
And let me guess.
You're Donna.

02:05.281 --> 02:08.532
Oh, you have no idea
how Donna I am.

02:08.667 --> 02:11.085
- Well, Donna, I'm Harvey--
- Harvey Specter.

02:11.203 --> 02:12.170
You really think
I'd be talking to you

02:12.254 --> 02:13.171
if I didn't know
who you were?

02:13.255 --> 02:15.039
And how exactly
do you know about me?

02:15.207 --> 02:16.040
I know about everybody.

02:16.175 --> 02:18.376
What I don't know is

02:18.510 --> 02:20.345
why this is the first case
you ever took to trial.

02:20.429 --> 02:21.829
Because it was
a white-collar crime,

02:21.880 --> 02:23.214
not some drug dealer
on a corner,

02:23.349 --> 02:24.629
which makes it
the kind of case--

02:24.683 --> 02:27.051
That puts your name
in the paper.

02:27.136 --> 02:28.656
You're not just a pretty face,
are you?

02:28.721 --> 02:31.222
No, I'm not.

02:31.357 --> 02:32.557
So maybe you should
buy me a drink,

02:32.691 --> 02:34.731
and we can continue
this conversation in the corner.

02:36.478 --> 02:37.979
Jay?

02:38.113 --> 02:45.987
♪ ♪

02:53.579 --> 02:55.099
Sean, what are you doing
in my building

02:55.164 --> 02:56.414
in the middle of the night?

02:56.498 --> 02:57.582
I thought we were done
with you following me.

02:57.750 --> 02:59.467
I'm not following you.

02:59.585 --> 03:01.469
I'm waiting for you.

03:01.587 --> 03:02.754
I need your help.

03:02.838 --> 03:04.839
<i>You</i> need my help,
or the SEC needs my help?

03:04.973 --> 03:05.973
We both do.

03:06.008 --> 03:07.342
But at the moment,
I care more about me

03:07.426 --> 03:09.310
than I do about the SEC.

03:09.428 --> 03:10.895
I can't find the money.

03:10.979 --> 03:12.230
What do you mean
you can't find the money?

03:12.314 --> 03:13.815
What the hell have you been
doing for the last three months?

03:13.932 --> 03:14.932
Looking for the money.

03:14.933 --> 03:15.983
Then look harder,

03:16.101 --> 03:17.902
because Woodall isn't
in the charity business.

03:17.986 --> 03:19.103
Forstman buys people,

03:19.188 --> 03:21.105
and we handed them to you
on a silver platter.

03:21.273 --> 03:22.357
And I stuck
my neck out for you,

03:22.491 --> 03:24.659
and I accused my friend
of being on the take.

03:24.777 --> 03:26.744
Now, if I can't follow through
with that, Eric Woodall walks.

03:26.862 --> 03:27.862
Charles Forstman walks.

03:27.946 --> 03:29.280
Well, what makes you think
I can find the money

03:29.365 --> 03:30.365
when you couldn't?

03:30.366 --> 03:31.582
I don't know
if you can or not,

03:31.700 --> 03:33.284
but they're gonna shut me down
in five days,

03:33.419 --> 03:34.836
and I need all the help
I can get.

03:42.961 --> 03:44.846
Okay, enough about me.
Let's talk about you.

03:44.963 --> 03:46.130
Ooh, my favorite subject.

03:46.215 --> 03:48.599
- You know what I think?
- Hmm?

03:48.717 --> 03:50.518
I think your favorite subject
didn't come up to me

03:50.636 --> 03:52.076
just to find out
why I went to trial.

03:52.137 --> 03:54.055
You want something.

03:54.139 --> 03:55.223
I sure do.

03:55.307 --> 03:58.810
And I think I might be ready
to give it to you.

03:58.894 --> 04:01.312
It's not sex.

04:01.397 --> 04:03.147
Then never mind.

04:04.733 --> 04:06.567
Wow, you're gonna be
that honest about it.

04:06.702 --> 04:09.203
Saves time.

04:09.321 --> 04:12.740
Well, in that case,
I want to move to your desk.

04:12.825 --> 04:13.875
And why is that?

04:13.992 --> 04:15.493
Because it's no secret
that in a few years,

04:15.577 --> 04:17.211
you're going back to Gordon,
Schmidt, and Van Dyke.

04:17.329 --> 04:19.630
And let me guess, you want to
come with me when I do.

04:19.714 --> 04:21.132
No, I don't.

04:21.250 --> 04:22.800
Then why?

04:22.885 --> 04:24.469
Because I'm gonna be
an actress,

04:24.553 --> 04:25.913
and I want somebody
who understands

04:26.004 --> 04:29.223
that there's more to life
than just the DA's office.

04:29.341 --> 04:30.675
And that I can give my all
to them

04:30.809 --> 04:32.727
but still step out
for the occasional audition.

04:32.845 --> 04:34.285
So you're stepping out
on me already?

04:34.313 --> 04:36.013
Yes, but
the important thing is,

04:36.098 --> 04:38.015
I'm telling you about it
in advance.

04:38.100 --> 04:39.851
Macallan 36.

04:39.985 --> 04:41.486
I didn't order
a Macallan 36.

04:41.603 --> 04:44.856
It's from the gentleman
over there.

04:44.990 --> 04:46.510
Okay, I don't know
who that is,

04:46.525 --> 04:49.410
but I'm telling you right now,
he is bad news.

04:55.367 --> 04:57.869
You look different.

04:57.953 --> 05:00.037
I will take that
as a compliment.

05:00.172 --> 05:01.956
I meant I wasn't expecting
to see you like that--

05:02.040 --> 05:03.374
I-I know what you meant.

05:03.509 --> 05:05.509
What you really meant is that
you weren't expecting

05:05.511 --> 05:06.878
to see me at all.

05:07.045 --> 05:08.429
Excuse me?

05:08.547 --> 05:09.931
Oh, come on, Harvey.

05:10.048 --> 05:11.528
Ever since Mike came back
to the firm,

05:11.550 --> 05:15.019
I've basically been
nonexistent to you.

05:15.103 --> 05:16.103
What's going on?

05:16.138 --> 05:18.055
Cahill can't find the money.

05:18.140 --> 05:19.857
What do you mean
he can't find the money?

05:19.942 --> 05:21.382
What's he been doing
this whole time?

05:21.443 --> 05:23.561
- Yeah, that's what I said.
- And what did he say?

05:23.645 --> 05:25.445
He said he's in trouble
and he needs our help.

05:25.447 --> 05:27.148
And I'm gonna tell you
what I couldn't tell him.

05:27.232 --> 05:28.449
He can't find the money

05:28.567 --> 05:30.327
because he's been looking
in the wrong place.

05:30.402 --> 05:32.403
So where's
the right place?

05:32.571 --> 05:34.622
I don't know exactly.

05:34.740 --> 05:37.492
But somewhere, there's a person
Eric Woodall cares about,

05:37.626 --> 05:38.743
and that's
where the money went.

05:38.827 --> 05:40.578
And why can't we tell
Cahill that?

05:40.662 --> 05:42.330
Because I don't know him to know
how I know it.

05:42.464 --> 05:44.665
- How do you know it?
- Because I know.

05:47.135 --> 05:48.753
You want a chance to exist?

05:48.887 --> 05:50.721
Figure out a way
to get this done.

05:55.811 --> 05:59.397
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

05:59.515 --> 06:02.733
♪ Get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

06:02.851 --> 06:05.903
♪ Everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

06:06.021 --> 06:09.657
♪ Everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

06:09.775 --> 06:12.577
♪ I'll even eat a bean pie,
I don't mind ♪

06:12.694 --> 06:16.581
♪ Me and Missy is
so busy, busy making money ♪

06:16.698 --> 06:18.032
♪ All right ♪

06:18.116 --> 06:19.670
♪ All step back,
I'm 'bout to dance ♪

